1 WHEREAS, the process of finding solutions to the issues surrounding the current management of
2 hunting seasons, including resident and nonresident license allocation, should include all stakeholders.
3
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
5
6 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Short title. [Sections 1 and 2] may be cited as the "Montana Hunters
7 First Act".
8
9 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Nonresident hunting impact study. (1) The department of fish, wildlife,
10 and parks shall conduct a study of nonresident impacts on deer, and elk, UPLAND GAME BIRD, AND WATER FOWL
11 hunting in the state and in each of the fish and wildlife commission's administrative regions.
12 (2) The study must utilize a range of data, including but not limited to hunter days, harvest
13 reporting, use of lands that are part of hunting access programs, hunting pressure on public lands, elk and deer
14 population trends, THE ACREAGE AND DURATION OF PRIVATE LAND LEASES FOR HUNTING PURPOSES, and licensing.
15 (3) Upon completion of the study, the department shall publish a report that is accessible to the
16 public. The report must include:
17 (a) a comprehensive assessment of the data as it relates to nonresident impacts on deer and elk
18 hunting in the state and in each of the commission's administrative regions;
19 (b) specific information about the methods used for collecting or acquiring data used in the report;
20 and
21 (c) the identification of specific issues for consideration by the legislature, department, and
22 commission concerning nonresident impacts on deer and elk hunting.
23 (4) The study and report must be completed by December 1, 2026.
24
25 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Termination. [Sections 1 and 2] terminate December 31, 2026.
